00:07:17,758 --> 00:07:19,799
So let's just look at Bungie's player character.

132
00:07:21,260 --> 00:07:24,962
Our player character is actually two characters in one.

133
00:07:25,002 --> 00:07:27,263
The first one is the third person player,

134
00:07:27,283 --> 00:07:30,465
which you see when your buddies are running around.

135
00:07:30,505 --> 00:07:31,805
You see them in the open world.

136
00:07:31,945 --> 00:07:35,647
Or you see yourself when you do like a super animation.

137
00:07:36,768 --> 00:07:38,529
And then we have the first person player, which

138
00:07:38,589 --> 00:07:40,229
is derived from the third person player.

139
00:07:40,770 --> 00:07:44,131
And that's just your arms, a player camera, a support

140
00:07:44,191 --> 00:07:45,232
object, and a weapon.

141
00:07:46,095 --> 00:07:47,936
And this is the stuff that you're going to actually see

142
00:07:48,996 --> 00:07:50,317
from your player view on your screen.

143
00:07:51,358 --> 00:07:54,139
Well, when we put these together,

144
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,761
you have your actual player character.

145
00:07:57,341 --> 00:08:00,883
So you have your first person arms and rig basically

146
00:08:00,963 --> 00:08:03,245
sitting on top of the third person rig.

147
00:08:03,765 --> 00:08:08,448
And we basically make all of the third person geometry

148
00:08:08,608 --> 00:08:11,729
above the waist non-renderable from the first person camera.

149
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:14,131
And because of that.

150
00:08:15,434 --> 00:08:19,195
If you ever wondered, like, this is what the first person character, what your player character

151
00:08:19,215 --> 00:08:19,935
actually looks like.

